Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Soak your @bamboo skewers{4} in
water (to prevent them from burning).

Chop the @potatoes{450%g} lengthways into 1cm slices, then chop into 1cm wide
chips (no need to peel).

Pop the chips onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @olive oil{for chips},
season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single
layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, bake on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}.
Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, quarter and peel the @red onion{1}(quartered and peeled), then separate
the layers. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).
Zest and halve the @lime{1}(zested and halved).

Drain the @king prawns{150%g}, then add them to a medium #bowl{} along with the
onion. Drizzle with @olive oil{} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Add half
the lime zest and half the garlic, then mix until well coated.

Thread the prawns and onion alternately onto the skewers (2 per person), then
pop them on a large baking tray lined with foil.

Bake on the middle shelf of your oven for ~{12-15%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw prawns. They're
> cooked when pink on the outside and opaque in the middle.

While everything's in the oven, make the chimichurri.

Roughly chop the @flat leaf parsley{1%bunch}(roughly chopped, stalks and all).
Halve the @red chilli{½}(halved lengthways, deseeded and finely chopped).

> Add less chilli if you'd prefer things milder.

Add the parsley and chilli to another medium bowl with a squeeze of lime juice,
remaining garlic, remaining lime zest, and the @olive oil{for chimichurri}.
Season with salt and pepper and mix well. Set aside for later.

== Lime Slaw ==

In a medium bowl, combine the @mayonnaise{32%g}, a good squeeze of lime juice,
the @sugar{½%tsp} and @olive oil{1%tbsp} for the dressing. Season with salt and
pepper and stir in the @coleslaw mix{120%g}. Set aside for now.

== To Serve ==

Once the prawns are cooked, remove from the oven and drizzle over the
@honey{1%tbsp}.

Just before you're ready to serve, add the @baby leaf mix{50%g} to the lime slaw
and toss together.

Share the prawn skewers between your serving plates. Drizzle over the chimichurri.
Serve with the chips and salad alongside. Enjoy!